🧪 Lab 01 - First HTTPS Intercept
Objective
Successfully intercept and modify an HTTPS request using Burp Suite.

Environment
Burp Suite Community Edition v2026.6
Burp Built-in Chromium Browser
Target: https://example.com
Procedure
Started Burp Suite.
Created a Temporary Project.
Used Burp Default Configuration.
Opened the built-in Chromium browser.
Enabled Intercept.
Visited:
https://example.com

Burp intercepted the request.
Captured Request
GET / HTTP/1.1

Host: example.com
Request Headers Observed
Host
User-Agent
Accept
Accept-Language
Accept-Encoding
Connection
Modification Performed
Original Request:

GET /
Modified Request:

GET /test
Server Response
404 Not Found
Observation
The server returned a 404 Not Found response because the requested endpoint /test did not exist.

This confirmed that:

Burp successfully intercepted the request.
The modified request reached the server.
The server processed the modified request.
